Two explanations explain why individuals conform: In order to fit in and be accepted by a group, individuals adhere to the beliefs or actions of others. People comply to the explicit or tacit standards or expectations of a group to fulfill social norms and to avoid undesirable repercussions. Normative impact happens regardless of the ambiguity of information. The following three elements impact conformity: Larger groups have a tendency to have more social impact on individuals. Individuals are more prone to comply when there is consensus within a group. People are more prone to adhere to the beliefs or practices of a group that they see as having a high status or being respected. 